        <body>       
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Aldine Hotel<lb/>
                March 18<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1884<lb/></p>
                
            <p>My Dear Morais&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>I enclose<lb/> Mr Vaux&#39;s reply to mine&#44;<lb/> and I am willing to assist<lb/> you if you think necessary&#45;&#45;<lb/> or if his friends will do it&#44;<lb/> perhaps it would be much<lb/> better. I have just return<lb/>&#45;ed from Port Richmond<lb/> visiting the school and dwel&#45;<lb/>lings of our Pariahs&#8212;In&#45;<lb/>deed the Alliance Israel&#45;<lb/>ite is badly needed here&#45;&#45;<lb/> Apropos let me say that<lb/> Mr David Sulzberger will<lb/> be in my room tomorrow<lb/> night&#44; and we will frame<lb/> a circular urging our<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>people to aid in establish&#45;<lb/>ing an industrial branch<lb/> which <hi rend="underline">should</hi> and <hi rend="underline">must</hi><lb/> be done to elevate the chil&#45;<lb/> dren from <sic>degredation</sic> and<lb/> misery&#45;&#45;I should be much<lb/> pleased if on Saturday you<lb/> would allude to it&#8212;Ask any<lb/> of those children 74 in num<lb/>ber at the school&#44; what does<lb/> your father do&#44; and the in&#45;<lb/> variable answer is&#44; he peddles&#45;&#45;<lb/> Now if one trade was begun&#44;<lb/> another would soon follow<lb/> and in time we all would<lb/> see the happy result. The<lb/> enterprise will require but<lb/> a comparatively small sum<lb/> say &#36;2000 and can it be<lb/> possible for this amount<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/> 
            <p>so good a cause should fail&#45;&#45;<lb/>
                With my kindest regards<lb/> to you and yours&#45;&#45;<lb/>
                I remain Truly&#45;&#45;<lb/>
                Lucien Moss.<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
